# Security Rules

## Secrets
- Never commit passwords, API keys, private keys, tokens, or session material.
- Use placeholders: `<API_KEY>`, `<WG_PRIVATE_KEY>`.
- Reference external secret locations; do not embed values.

## Operational Security
- Do not commit malware samples or memory dumps.
- Hash-only sample registries are allowed.
- Redact customer/personal data from case notes before commit.

## Trust Boundaries
- Document zone assumptions explicitly (Edge/Core/Lab/Management).
- Lab compromise must not be treated as equivalent to management access.
- VPN and firewall changes require rationale notes.

## Detection & IR Safety
- Validation commands must be safe for lab context.
- Do not provide exploit PoCs intended for unauthorized systems.
- Prefer defensive engineering guidance.

## Alignment
- Follow [[STANDARDS]] and [[ARCHITECTURE]].
